HEADWORD: Egoistical
<hw>E`go*is"tic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to egoism; imbued
with egoism or excessive thoughts of self; self-loving.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ill-natured feeling, or <qex>egoistic</qex> pleasure in making men
miserable.</q> <rj><qau>G. Eliot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Egoistically</ent>⟦br⟧
